===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*ḱley-|id=incline}}
From {{inh|en|enm|declinen}}, and ultimately {{der|en|la|declīnō|t=to bend, turn aside, deflect, inflect, decline}}, from {{m|la|de||down}} + {{m|la|clīnō||I bend, I incline}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ḱley-}} (English {{m|en|lean}}). The senses arrived from two separate pathways in Middle English:
* The grammatical sense came from {{inh|en|ang|declīnian}}, which was borrowed directly from the Latin etymon.
* All senses except the grammatical sense were derived from those of {{der|en|fro|decliner}}. Old French itself borrowed the verb from Latin.

